<main id="main">
<!-- Panui / Intro -->
<section id="panui" class="rule">
<div class="panui">
<p><strong>Pānui (Notice):</strong> This one-page gathers everything from the original site in a calm, easy-to-read format. No plays, no long asides. Just what’s needed to help you decide your vote.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“O ye lovers of God! Make firm your steps; fulfil your pledge to one another; go forth in harmony to scatter abroad the sweet savours of God’s love, and to establish His Teachings, until ye breathe a soul into the dead body of this world, and bring true healing in the physical and spiritual realms to everyone who aileth.”</p>
<footer>— ‘Abdu’l-Bahá</footer>
</blockquote>
</div>

<p><strong>Why I’m running:</strong> Rates are rising faster than value. Core services—water, roads, safety—must come first. Let’s fix the basics, be honest about costs, and keep local money working for local people.</p>
</section>

<!-- What it Means for You -->
<section id="what-it-means" class="rule">
<h2>What it means for you</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Fair rates:</strong> Slow the growth of rates by cutting low-value spending and phasing projects sensibly.</li>
<li><strong>Safer streets:</strong> Better lighting, quicker fixes for hotspots, and design that protects people.</li>
<li><strong>More homes:</strong> Faster consents, small smart subdivisions, and simple standard plans to cut costs.</li>
<li><strong>Plain English council:</strong> Short reports, clear budgets, open books you can read in minutes.</li>
<li><strong>Local money stays local:</strong> A community-owned Hamilton Bank to keep interest here supporting basics.</li>
</ul>
</section>

<!-- Priorities -->
<section id="priorities" class="rule">
<h2>Priorities</h2>

<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>1) Fair rates & real value</h3>
<ul>
<li>Simple budget dashboard: what we spend, what we pause, and why.</li>
<li>Review all projects; fund those that help the most people soonest.</li>
<li>Strong hardship help so people can stay in their homes.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>2) Safer streets</h3>
<ul>
<li>Fix dark spots first; replace broken lights and tidy overgrowth.</li>
<li>Target high-risk areas with police support and privacy-respecting cameras.</li>
<li>Design calm streets where people live, walk, and bike.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>3) More homes people can afford</h3>
<ul>
<li>Clear checklists and time limits for consents.</li>
<li>Unlock small, well-served areas close to jobs and services.</li>
<li>Publish low-cost standard house plans to speed builds.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>4) Open LIMs & faster answers</h3>
<ul>
<li>Make LIMs cheaper and easier to read.</li>
<li>Free map layers online: flood, pipes, heritage, consents.</li>
<li>One point of contact for your case—no run-around.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- Hamilton Bank -->
<section id="bank" class="rule">
<h2>Hamilton Bank (community-owned)</h2>
<p>This is a simple local bank model. It keeps more interest payments in Hamilton and uses profits to lower debt and fund basics.</p>

<div class="grid">
<div class="card">
<h3>How it works</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Local deposits:</strong> People and groups can save with the bank.</li>
<li><strong>Local lending:</strong> Plain home loans and safe, council-backed projects.</li>
<li><strong>Low overheads:</strong> Digital-first, small team, strong risk rules.</li>
<li><strong>Profits stay here:</strong> Lower council debt and support water, roads, libraries.</li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Safeguards</h3>
<ul>
<li>Independent board and strict lending standards.</li>
<li>Quarterly reports in plain English.</li>
<li>Step-by-step build: start small, prove the model, grow carefully.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<ul>
<li>More of our money works for Hamilton instead of leaving town.</li>
<li>Lower borrowing costs over time with steady discipline.</li>
<li>Transparent books you can actually read.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<p class="muted">Bottom line: keep local money working for local people. Clear rules. No tricks.</p>
</section>

<!-- How to Vote -->
<section id="how-to-vote" class="rule">
<h2>How to vote (STV, postal)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Rank candidates 1, 2, 3… in your true order.</li>
<li>Do not repeat or skip numbers. If you make a mistake, cross it once and write the correct number.</li>
<li>Post or drop your vote in on time. Check council dates for Hamilton.</li>
</ul>
<a class="cta" href="https://www.hamilton.govt.nz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Check voting info</a>
</section>

